 ## Tech Stack
 ### Django
 Main webserver, handles backend auth, game fetching etc

 ### Celery + Redis
 Handles the analysis task

 ### Stockfish + FastAPI
 This is a separate server which helps me to support my positional algorithm with stockfish to ensure that I'm highlighting the correct moves, and influences the results of the algorithm as well. This is a cluster of optimized stockfish instances at lower depths to increase evaluation speeds. Repo Link: [https://github.com/someonewhoexists1210/StockfishWorker](https://github.com/someonewhoexists1210/StockfishWorker)

 ### Frontend: React + Vite + Tailwindcss
 I feel like this is the default for webapps now. I have to admit a good chunk of the designing was done by AI (I know im sorry) but tbf im in the middle of exams and was pretty exhausted making the backend, plus im despise frontend work. Though I made many edits of my own to make it feel real. This is hosted on cloudflare pages/workers
 Repo link: [https://github.com/someonewhoexists1210/DeepPly-Frontend](https://github.com/someonewhoexists1210/DeepPly-Frontend)

